gomodel:SYNGO_606  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Supplemental table S1 contains 698 synaptic proteins identified in three different experimental approaches: isolated PSD preparation, MAGUK-associated signalling complexes (MASC) and AMPA receptor complexes (ARCs).\nRL5_MOUSE was found in the isolated PSD fraction.\nFor proteins coming from datasets derived from PSD (detergent-resistant synaptic junctions) preparations without defined selection / enrichment of the pre- or postsynaptic compartment we cannot assign these proteins to excitatory and/or inhibitory nor to the presynapse or / and postsynapse without further information.. Experimental description: Here we present a large-scale proteomic analysis of the\npostsynaptic proteome (PSP) of mouse brain. p.17" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2017-06-12" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_606" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

